    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Unfortunately this comes from the Horn solver used by the CHC engine. Apparently just adding an SMT Array (used by the Solidity `mapping`) to the predicates (even though they are only passed around and not used in any constraints) makes the solver return `unknown`. In this case, the BMC engine is used, and since it doesn't have knowledge about contract invariants it returns this false positive.\r\nI'm going to try the current development version of the solver to see if the problem persists, and in that case open an issue with them.\r\nThanks for reporting!",
